Abdomen blackish brown; all setae yellowish, longest dorsally on pregenital tergites. Genitalia (
Fig. 4
) blackish with phallus and parameral sheath yellow. Major lobe of cercus (
Figs. 2, 4
) petiolate basally, much broader apically, with stout spine-like setae and finer bristles apically; smaller basal lobe apically narrow with small apical spine. Phallus strongly curved apically.

Wing (
Fig. 5
) membrane clear, veins yellowish.
